body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for contacting Car Dealership Support. My name is Dennis Lopez. May I kindly have your name?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, my name is Madison Kelly.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Madison. Could you please provide me with your contact number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's five five five - six six six - seven seven seven.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Madison. And could you also share your email address with me?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for sharing that. Is there anything else I can assist you with today, Madison?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all. Just hoping to resolve this data management issue.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I understand. I will ensure our team looks into it. Thank you for your time, Madison. Have a great day.
